RECIPE to run PhotonAnalysisUtils on release 15.5.0
valid only for PhotonAnalysisUtils stricly below 00-00-38 (up to 00-00-37 included)
===================================================

* configure athena for release 15.5.0 

* check out and compile additional packages needed for bugfixes for the photon recovery tool

        cmt co -r egammaEvent-03-03-26 Reconstruction/egamma/egammaEvent
        cd Reconstruction/egamma/egammaEvent/cmt
        make
        cd -

        cmt co -r egammaCaloTools-00-00-24 Reconstruction/egamma/egammaCaloTools
        cd Reconstruction/egamma/egammaCaloTools/cmt
        make
        cd -

        cmt co -r PhotonAnalysisAlgs-00-01-33 Reconstruction/egamma/egammaAnalysis/PhotonAnalysisAlgs
        cd Reconstruction/egamma/egammaAnalysis/PhotonAnalysisAlgs/cmt
        make
        cd -

* check out HEAD version of PhotonAnalysisUtils and compile:

	cmt co PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils
	cd PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/cmt
	make
	cd -


* ... and be optimistic: Run! 

	mkdir run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.py run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.root run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.txt run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.dat run
	cd run
	ln -s <your-favourite-AOD> AOD.pool.root
	athena.py PAUanalysis_jobOptions.py

===> NOTE: PAUanalysis_jobOptions.py is set up to perform photon recovery with official tool, 
           and trigger access. Change the options at your need, in the beginning of this file

